<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro _MHD_UNPOISON_MEMORY is defined as a no-op ((void)0) and is invoked in functions such as MHD_pool_destroy. Each invocation executes an operation that has no effect at runtime; removing the macro call would not change program behaviour. Therefore these invocations constitute dead code (e.g. the line "_MHD_UNPOISON_MEMORY(pool->memory, pool->size);" in MHD_pool_destroy).
</scenario>
